  "opinion": "As a 90-year-old man from Bari, retired and living a quiet life with my wife, I've seen many health crises come and go, but the COVID-19 pandemic was something truly unique. Managing discussions about healthcare and COVID vaccines requires a blend of patience, respect, and practical wisdom, especially at my age. First and foremost, I believe in listening more than speaking. In my long life, I've learned that everyone has their own experiences and fears, and dismissing them only leads to conflict. When talking about vaccines, I start by acknowledging the concerns of others, whether they're about side effects or mistrust in authorities. My approach is rooted in my Islamic faith, which teaches compassion and community care—vaccination, to me, is a way to protect not just myself but my neighbors in Bari, much like how we look out for each other in our close-knit community. I avoid social media, so my information comes from trusted sources like local doctors and health officials, which helps me stay grounded in facts without the noise of online debates. In discussions, I share my own experience: getting vaccinated was a decision made with my family and doctor, considering my age and health. I emphasize the importance of consulting healthcare professionals rather than relying on rumors. My hobbies, like baking and knitting, have taught me patience and attention to detail—qualities that serve me well in these conversations. I don't push my views aggressively; instead, I offer gentle guidance, much like how I'd teach someone a new recipe or a knitting pattern. At 90, I've seen how fear can divide people, but I also know that kindness and clear communication can bridge gaps. In Bari, where community ties are strong, I've found that face-to-face talks over a cup of coffee work best. I remind others that vaccines are tools for safety, developed through rigorous science, and that protecting our health is a shared responsibility. Ultimately, managing these discussions is about balancing firmness in my beliefs with empathy for others, ensuring we all move forward together in health and harmony.",
